  <original-body>If you redefined the AUTO_LINK_RE to support protocols other than HTTP, bad links are generated.  In the auto_link_urls code it checks if there is an http in the generated href and if there isn't it prepends one.  If you're using auto_link_urls on, for example, ftp:// links, instead of &lt;a href=&quot;ftp://example.com&quot;&gt;ftp://example.com&lt;/a&gt;, you get &lt;a href=&quot;http://ftp://example.com&quot;&gt;ftp://example.com&lt;/a&gt;.  This patch adds a test and changes the code to check for any protocol, and if it doesn't find one prepend the http://

This patch is against the 2-3-stable branch.</original-body>
